Steelmaker Cap Plans Buyback of Chile Inflation-Linked Bonds

-- B y   S e b a s t i a n   B o y d
-- 
2011-04-29T18:52:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/steelmaker-cap-plans-buyback-of-chile-inflation-linked-bonds.html
Cap SA,  Chile ’s biggest steelmaker,
will offer to buy back $94 million of inflation-linked bonds
first sold May 15, 2008. The bonds are due to mature in 2013.  CAP announced the plan in a statement published on the
website of the country’s securities regulator.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sebastian Boyd in Santiago at 
